PIZZA BOX (05/02/2026)

Players first aquire an adequit piece of cardboard for the Game.
Players a d20 dice to determine playing order. Players then take turns throwing a quarter / bottlecap onto the cardboard.

If it is a players first time landing on an empty space on the board, then they write their name where their piece lands and draw a
circle the size of their palm around it.

If it is a players second time landing on an empty space on the board then the player writes a rule or challange and an 
appropriate reward. (Ex 1 Tally). The player then draws a shape around it no bigger than their hand.

If a player lands on another players namespace, then the namespace owner takes 1 drink and draws 1 tally in their circle.

If a player lands on a challange / rule they have two options:

    Complete the rule / challange and recieve the reward or 1 tally.
    or
    Do NOT complete it and take X amount of drinks, where X is the number of tallys you have.

The Game continues until the board becomes full, once full each player gets 3 more throws and the game ends. If there is a tie,
tied player compete in a flash round to determine the winner.

The player with the most tallys at the end of the Game wins and gets 1 ZORK!